<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code> element contains one or more <a href="/docs/elements/native/tr/"><code>&lt;tr&gt;</code></a> elements that make up the data portion of a table. It should appear after <a href="/docs/elements/native/thead/"><code>&lt;thead&gt;</code></a> and before <a href="/docs/elements/native/tfoot/"><code>&lt;tfoot&gt;</code></a> in the source order.</p>
    <p>Vanilla Breeze applies row hover effects to tbody rows and uses tbody for the <code>.striped</code> variant's alternating background colors.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Every data table:</strong> All tables should use tbody to group data rows</li>
      <li><strong>Multiple tbody sections:</strong> Group related rows for visual or semantic separation</li>
      <li><strong>Dynamic content:</strong> Easier to target and update data rows separately from headers</li>
      <li><strong>Scripting:</strong> JavaScript can easily target tbody for adding/removing rows</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

